Package xyz.msws.nope.modules.actions.actions

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddVLAction
    Adds VL to the player
    AnimationAction
    Runs an animation and then the ActionGroup after it is done
    BanAction
    Bans, saves logs, and increments statistics
    BanwaveAction
    Queues the player for a banwave
    CancelAction
    Teleports the player to their CPlayer.getLastSafeLocation() This naturally means it doesn't work against certain check types such as KillAura
    CommandAction
    Makes the player run a command
    CustomAction
    Used to signify a custom action that the config has set, this is extremely useful
    DelayAction
    A useful AbstractConditionalAction for avoiding spam or kicking the player but not every time they flag a hack.
    IsDevCheck
    An AbstractConditionalAction that returns true if the plugin is in dev mode.
    KickAction
    Kicks the player with the specified reason.
    LogAction
    Logs the specified message to either CONSOLE, FILE, or INGAME.
    MessageAction
    Sends a message to a specified target.
    MessagePlayerAction
    Accessibility option that is effectively just MessageAction but targets only the player.
    NotDevCheck
    An AbstractConditionalAction that returns false if the plugin is in dev mode.
    PingCheck
    Another AbstractConditionalAction that is used for checking the player's ping.
    RandomCheck
    AbstractConditionalAction Used for random actions.
    SetVLAction
    Sets the player VL to the specified value
    TPSCheck
    Used for checking the server's TPS
    VLActionCheck
    The biggest and most useful check, used for checking the current VL that the player is at for the specified hack
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    LogAction.Type
